column5: slate falls is handling hooker lake, any suggestions on size of fish in lake?

14-19 inch walleye are very abundant. 20-23 inch walleye usually get at least couple a day 24-26 inch walleye occasionally I am aware of a few in the 28 inch range. Seen a lot of 15+ pound northers over the years. Usually at least one a year but not always.
